The above anslysis using linear and non-linear clasiification models show a clear issue arsing from class imbalance of classes - different types of "wine variant".

In our next approach we are going to try to combine the different categories of wines that are under represented in the given data.

Working with class imablance

In[15]:
def recategorize(df):
    df['wine_variant'] =np.where(df['wine_variant'].isin(['Riesling','Sauvignon Blanc']),'Riesling/Sauvignon Blanc', df['wine_variant'])
    df['wine_variant'] =np.where(df['wine_variant'].isin(['Merlot','Syrah']),'Merlot/Syrah', df['wine_variant'])
    df['wine_variant'] =np.where(df['wine_variant'].isin(['Cabernet Sauvignon','Zinfandel']),'Cabernet Sauvignon/Zinfandel', df['wine_variant'])
